{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492621"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:38:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:38:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1114"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1114","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1114"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.65,0.09,0.01,0.07,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1114"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41754"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1114","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1114"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1114"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26690"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"912"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"624"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1024"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3469"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10754"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/41754"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 63-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a two day history of worsening dyspnoea, associated with a cough and headache. One month ago she was diagnosed with metastatic non-small cell carcinoma of the lung. On examination her face is swollen and a suffused pink colour, and this is exacerbated on bending forward. There is an stridor and she cannot speak. She is given oxygen by face mask and intravenous furosemide. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial treatment to consider?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Corticosteroids","Therapeutic Anticoagulation","Ceftriaxone","Chemotherapy","Radiotherapy"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient is experiencing superior vena cava (SVC) obstruction secondary to the lung cancer. The goals of managing SVC syndrome is to alleviate symptoms and treat the underlying cause. In patients who present with life-threatening symptoms, it is essential to stabilise them first by securing the airway, supporting breathing and circulation, as well as immediate recanalisation with placement of stent. \u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroids\u003C/strong\u003E play an important role in the initial management, as they reduce tumour swelling and may assist in reducing the degree of obstruction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn patients who are haemodynamically stable, then next treatment step depends on the underlying cause. \u003Cstrong\u003ERadiotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E plays a major role in symptom control and is more efficacious than chemotherapy in non-small cell carcinoma of the lung. If the underlying problem was small cell carcinoma or Hodgkin\u0027s lymphoma, then \u003Cstrong\u003Echemotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E might be more efficacious.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMore than 80% of SVC case are the result of mediastinal involvement with malignancy; most often carcinoma of the bronchus. \u003Cstrong\u003EAnticoagulation \u003C/strong\u003Emight be appropriate if a vascular aetiology was likely - but this is almost certainly not the case with this patient. There is no evidence that this patient has an infectious process and hence antibiotic \u003Cstrong\u003Eceftriaxone \u003C/strong\u003Eis also not recommended.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Given as soon as the patient presents, steroids have an important initial role in the reduction of tumour size and overcoming obstructive symptoms."],"references":["Yu J, Wilson L, MD, Detterbeck F. Superior Vena Cava Syndrome\u2014A Proposed Classification System and Algorithm for Management. J Thorac Oncol. 2008;3(8):811-814. Available at: https://www.jto.org/article/S1556-0864(15)30443-3/pdf","Planchard S, Popat K, Kerr S, Novello E, Smit C, Faivre-Finn T, et. al. Metastatic non-small cell lung cancer: ESMO Clinical Practice Guidelines for diagnosis, treatment and follow-up. European Society for Medical Oncology. 2018;29(4):iv192\u2013iv237. Available at: https://www.esmo.org/content/download/347819/6934778/1/ESMO-CPG-mNSCLC-15SEPT2020.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26690"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1114"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26690","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/26690"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-01-23T08:26:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-29T09:11:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1114"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41754"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links"